
# Logs, Python, SQLite, sentiment + PP data (large CSVs, generated)
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
*.log
*.pyc
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
__pycache__/
public_pulse_data/
sentiment_data/*.csv

# Price cache (hundreds of MB, 2600 CSV files) — never ship to runtime
data_cache/prices/
# SEC XBRL fact dumps (5GB+, per-company) — never ship to runtime
data_cache/sec_edgar/facts/
# Upside-hunt CSV ground truth (can be regenerated; MB-scale)
data_cache/public_pulse/
# Everything else under data_cache/ (runtime JSONs, profiles, SEC metadata)
# gets shipped — the files are small and the API reads them on every
# request. Note: negations on sub-paths of an excluded parent dir do NOT
# work, so we list specific heavy subdirs rather than try to exclude the
# whole tree and re-include files.

# Backtest result artifacts (large, reproducible from scripts)
*_backtest*.csv
*_backtest*.md
phase_c_reproduction*.csv
phase_c_reproduction*.md
upside_hunt_results.csv
upside_hunt_scored.csv
upside_hunt_report.md

# Overnight / ad-hoc run logs
overnight_v*_status.txt
overnight_v*.log
price_backfill.log
macro_combined_run.log

# Claude Code internals
.claude/worktrees/
